    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="649"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to the <persName
                            type="to">Duke de Arcos</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: It gives me pleasure to take this
                    personal way of informing you that I am advised by the Secretary of War that
                    General Otis reports that there were shipped to Spain on December 13, on the <hi
                        rend="italic">Cachemire</hi>, 30 Spanish officers and 1,067 enlisted men;
                    May 6, on the <hi rend="italic">Cataluna</hi>, 71 officers and 30 men; May 30,
                    on the <hi rend="italic">Leon XIII</hi>, 4 officers and 6 men; June 3, on the
                        <hi rend="italic">Satrustegui</hi>, 11 officers and 79 men; July 1, on the
                        <hi rend="italic">Isla de Luzon</hi>, 13 officers and 16 men.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
